values.name: format
values.comment:
Use a format string to format a time. See the
[README](https://github.com/mgold/elm-date-format/blob/master/README.md) for a
list of accepted formatters.

name: Date.Format
comment:
Format strings for dates.

@docs format, localFormat, formatISO8601

values.name: format
values.comment:
Use a format string to format a date. See the
[README](https://github.com/mgold/elm-date-format/blob/master/README.md) for a
list of accepted formatters.

values.name: formatISO8601
values.comment:
Formats a UTC date acording to
[ISO-8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601). This is commonly used to
send dates to a server. For example: `2016-01-06T09:22:00Z`.

values.name: localFormat
values.comment:
Use a localization record and a format string to format a date. See the
[README](https://github.com/mgold/elm-date-format/blob/master/README.md) for a
list of accepted formatters.

name: Date.Local

aliases.name: Local
aliases.comment:
A collection of strings and formats for localizing formats.

Time zones and default formats are not implemented,
but included to avoid possible version conflicts in the future.
aliases.type: { date : { months : Date.Local.Months , monthsAbbrev : Date.Local.Months , wdays : Date.Local.WeekDays , wdaysAbbrev : Date.Local.WeekDays , defaultFormat : Maybe.Maybe String } , time : { am : String , pm : String , defaultFormat : Maybe.Maybe String } , timeZones : Maybe.Maybe Date.Local.TimeZones , defaultFormat : Maybe.Maybe String }

aliases.name: Months
aliases.comment: A record of names for the months of the year.
aliases.type: { jan : String , feb : String , mar : String , apr : String , may : String , jun : String , jul : String , aug : String , sep : String , oct : String , nov : String , dec : String }

aliases.name: TimeZones
aliases.comment:
Maps from %z type string (+hhmm or -hhmm) to timezone name or abbreviation.

Not currently implemented.

aliases.name: WeekDays
aliases.comment: A record of names for the days of the week.
aliases.type: { mon : String , tue : String , wed : String , thu : String , fri : String , sat : String , sun : String }
